<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM3.10.10">
<l>ceṉṟuciṉa viṭaiyēḻum paṭavaṭarttup piṉṉai cevvittōḷ puṇarntukanta tirumāltaṉ kōyil</l>
<l>aṉṟayaṉu maraṉcēyu maṉaiyavarkaḷ nāṅkū rarimēya viṇṇakara mamarntaceḻuṅ kuṉṟai</l>
<l>kaṉṟineṭu vēlvalavaṉ maṅkaiyartaṅ kōmāṉ kalikaṉṟi yolimālai yaintiṉoṭu mūṉṟum</l>
<l>oṉṟiṉoṭu moṉṟumivai kaṟṟuvallā rulakattuttamarkaṭ kuttamarā yumparumā varkaḷē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who, learning these five-with-three and one-with-one [verses],</l>
<l rend="indent">master [this] garland of words of Kalikaṉṟi,</l>
<l>King of those of Maṅkai, the one skilled with the raging, long lance,</l>
<l rend="indent">about the splendid mountain[-like lord]</l>
<l>Seated in Arimēya Viṇṇakaram in Nānkūr [where dwell]</l>
<l rend="indent">those who are like the Unborn and Hara’s child,</l>
<l>The temple of Tirumāl who rejoiced embracing the beautiful arms of Piṉṉai,</l>
<l rend="indent">having attacked seven bulls who came in anger, so they perished,</l>
<l rend="indent">as the best of the best in the world, they will become celestials.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
